    <section id="fs-id1959412" type="problems-exercises" class="problems-exercises"><title>Problem Exercises</title><exercise id="fs-id2756436" type="problem-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2756393"><para id="import-auto-id2607520">Find the momentum of a helium nucleus having a mass of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>68</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>–27</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext> kg</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{6 "." "68" times "10" rSup { size 8{"27"} } " kg"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> that is moving at <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>200</m:mtext><m:mi>c</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{0 "." "200"c} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id2999155">
