  <glossary>
    <definition id="import-auto-id1509292"><term>relativistic momentum</term> <meaning id="fs-id2005074"><m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>p</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{p} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, the momentum of an object moving at relativistic velocity; <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>p</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mstyle fontstyle="italic"><m:mrow><m:mtext>γmu</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{p= ital "γmu"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, where <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{m} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is the rest mass of the object, <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>u</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{u} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is its velocity relative to an observer, and the relativistic factor <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>γ</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:msqrt><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:msup><m:mi>u</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:msup><m:mi>c</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:msqrt></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{γ= {  {1}  over  { sqrt {1 -  {  {u rSup { size 8{2} } }  over  {c rSup { size 8{2} } } } } } } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></meaning></definition>

<definition id="fs-id1372954"><term>rest mass</term> <meaning id="fs-id1819588">the mass of an object as measured by a person at rest relative to the object</meaning></definition>

    </glossary>
